The '''Elven-way''' was the highroad<ref name=rings>{{S|Rings}}</ref> that ran from [[Ost-in-Edhil]]<ref name=rings/> in the Elven realm of [[Eregion]],<ref name="elvenway">{{FR|Journey}}, p. 303</ref> along the course of the [[Sirannon]] stream<ref>{{FR|Journey}}, p. 300</ref> to the eastern end of Eregion, which was marked<ref name="elvenway" /> by two tall Holly trees that stood before the [[Doors of Durin]] of the underground dwarven realm of [[Moria]]<ref>{{FR|Journey}}, p. 302</ref>. In the year {{TA|3019}} of the late [[Third Age]], the [[Fellowship of the Ring]] used the Elven-way on their approach to the Doors of Durin.<ref>{{FR|Journey}}, pp. 300-3</ref>

